  {
    question: 'Which Italian regions have the highest and lowest tax surcharges?',
    answer: 'As of 2026, <strong>Lazio</strong> has the highest addizionale regionale at 3.33% (for incomes above approximately &euro;50,000), while several regions such as <strong>Lombardia, Veneto, and Friuli-Venezia Giulia</strong> remain among the lowest, with base rates around 1.23%. Regions with special autonomy statutes (e.g., Trentino-Alto Adige, Valle d\'Aosta) may apply different rates. For the municipal surcharge, it varies city by city -- Milan charges 0.8%, Rome charges 0.9%, and some smaller municipalities charge 0%.',
